  "prompt": "How much does it cost to register a trademark in the U.S.?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the cost to register a trademark in the United States can vary based on several factors, including the type of application and the number of classes in which you want to register your trademark. Generally, the fees are as follows:\n\n1. **TEAS Plus application**: $250 per class\n2. **TEAS Standard application**: $350 per class\n\nThe Trademark Electronic Application System (TEAS) Plus requires more information upfront and has stricter requirements, while TEAS Standard allows more flexibility but comes with a higher filing fee.\n\nThese are the basic filing fees, and additional costs may be incurred for things like attorney fees, responding to office actions, or filing statements of use. Always check the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) website for the most current fee schedule and details.",
